Note:
VERSION_SPEC - SemVer 2.0.0 + range/constraint surface (Tier 1)

This module provides the canonical version-specification surface for
the package manifest system, layered on the SemVer primitives in
version_constraint.runa. The two-layer split exists because:

  - version_constraint.runa owns the binary record layout for Version
    and Constraint (allocation, accessors, parse, satisfaction).
  - version_spec.runa adds high-level convenience APIs callers actually
    use day-to-day (intersection, range-to-string), and exposes a
    canonical type-name surface ("Version", "version_satisfies(v, spec)")
    so manifest consumers don't have to know the underlying record
    names.

This module re-exports every primitive from version_constraint with the
canonical names from the universal substrate spec:

  version_parse(string)                  -> Version
  version_compare(a, b)                  -> -1 / 0 / 1
  version_satisfies(v, spec_string)      -> 0 / 1
  version_range_intersect(a_spec, b_spec) -> spec string or 0 if empty
  version_range_to_string(spec)           -> human-readable form

Internally we forward each call to version_constraint, parsing the
caller's spec_string into a Constraint when needed.

References:
  - SemVer 2.0.0          https://semver.org/
  - Cargo version specs   https://doc.rust-lang.org/cargo/reference/specifying-dependencies.html
  - npm semver            https://github.com/npm/node-semver
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_primitive.runa" as StringPrim
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/string_builder.runa" as SB
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/manifest/version_constraint.runa" as VC

Note: ============================================================================
Note: VERSION PARSE / COMPARE - re-export
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Parse a SemVer string into a Version record. Delegates to
version_constraint.version_parse.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Forward call.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(|text|).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on malformed input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "version_parse" takes text as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc version_parse from VC with text
End Process

@Reasoning
Free a Version record returned by version_parse.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Forward to version_destroy_deep.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Safe on null.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "version_destroy" takes v as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc version_destroy_deep from VC with v
End Process

@Reasoning
Compare two Versions; returns -1 if a<b, 0 if equal, 1 if a>b.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Forward to version_constraint.version_compare.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over prerelease tokens.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null inputs.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "version_compare" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc version_compare from VC with a, b
End Process

@Reasoning
Convenience: return the version as its canonical textual form.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Forward to version_constraint.version_to_string.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "version_to_string" takes v as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc version_to_string from VC with v
End Process

@Reasoning
Test whether a Version satisfies a textual constraint spec like "^1.2.3"
or ">=1.0 <2.0".
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Parse the spec into a Constraint, call version_satisfies, destroy the
Constraint, return the boolean.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(|spec|+|version|).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null inputs or malformed spec.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "version_satisfies" takes v as Integer, spec_string as Integer returns Integer:
    If v is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If spec_string is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let constraint be proc constraint_parse from VC with spec_string
    If constraint is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let result be proc version_satisfies from VC with v, constraint
    proc constraint_destroy_deep from VC with constraint
    Return result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: VERSION RANGE OPERATIONS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Compute the intersection of two version-range specs. Returns the
canonical-form string of the intersection, or 0 if empty.

For two ranges a and b, the intersection is the set of versions
satisfying both. The result is rendered as a single composite
">=lo <hi" range when both inputs reduce to a closed numeric interval.

If either input is "*" (Any), the result is the other spec.
If either input is an Exact version, the result is that version iff
the other range admits it, otherwise empty.

For the general case we sample a small canonical lattice of
versions across the union of bounds: the intersection is computed by
parsing each spec, comparing bounds, and taking the more-restrictive
endpoints.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Parse both specs into Constraint records. Examine constraint kinds:
  - KIND_ANY:    intersection = other
  - KIND_EXACT:  intersection = exact iff it satisfies the other
  - both ranges: take max(lower_a, lower_b) and min(upper_a, upper_b);
                 emit as ">=<lo> <<hi>" string. If lower > upper, empty.
  - other combos (caret, tilde, wildcard): we synthesize a string of
    the form ">=<lower-bound-of-spec> <<exclusive-upper-of-spec>" for
    each, then intersect numerically.
Free the parsed constraints. Return the new string.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(|a|+|b|).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null inputs or malformed specs.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "version_range_intersect" takes a_spec as Integer, b_spec as Integer returns Integer:
    If a_spec is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If b_spec is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let a_eq be proc string_equals from StringCore with a_spec, "*"
    If a_eq is equal to 1:
        Return proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with b_spec
    End If
    Let b_eq be proc string_equals from StringCore with b_spec, "*"
    If b_eq is equal to 1:
        Return proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with a_spec
    End If
    Let ca be proc constraint_parse from VC with a_spec
    Let cb be proc constraint_parse from VC with b_spec
    If ca is equal to 0:
        If cb is not equal to 0:
            proc constraint_destroy_deep from VC with cb
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    If cb is equal to 0:
        proc constraint_destroy_deep from VC with ca
        Return 0
    End If
    Let lower_a be proc lower_bound_string with ca, a_spec
    Let upper_a be proc upper_bound_string with ca, a_spec
    Let lower_b be proc lower_bound_string with cb, b_spec
    Let upper_b be proc upper_bound_string with cb, b_spec

    Let chosen_lo be lower_a
    If lower_a is equal to 0:
        Set chosen_lo to lower_b
    Otherwise:
        If lower_b is not equal to 0:
            Let lo_a_v be proc version_parse from VC with lower_a
            Let lo_b_v be proc version_parse from VC with lower_b
            If lo_a_v is not equal to 0:
                If lo_b_v is not equal to 0:
                    Let cmp be proc version_compare from VC with lo_a_v, lo_b_v
                    If cmp is less than 0:
                        Set chosen_lo to lower_b
                    Otherwise:
                        Set chosen_lo to lower_a
                    End If
                End If
            End If
            If lo_a_v is not equal to 0:
                proc version_destroy_deep from VC with lo_a_v
            End If
            If lo_b_v is not equal to 0:
                proc version_destroy_deep from VC with lo_b_v
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Let chosen_hi be upper_a
    If upper_a is equal to 0:
        Set chosen_hi to upper_b
    Otherwise:
        If upper_b is not equal to 0:
            Let hi_a_v be proc version_parse from VC with upper_a
            Let hi_b_v be proc version_parse from VC with upper_b
            If hi_a_v is not equal to 0:
                If hi_b_v is not equal to 0:
                    Let cmp2 be proc version_compare from VC with hi_a_v, hi_b_v
                    If cmp2 is greater than 0:
                        Set chosen_hi to upper_b
                    Otherwise:
                        Set chosen_hi to upper_a
                    End If
                End If
            End If
            If hi_a_v is not equal to 0:
                proc version_destroy_deep from VC with hi_a_v
            End If
            If hi_b_v is not equal to 0:
                proc version_destroy_deep from VC with hi_b_v
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Let empty_check be 0
    If chosen_lo is not equal to 0:
        If chosen_hi is not equal to 0:
            Let lo_v be proc version_parse from VC with chosen_lo
            Let hi_v be proc version_parse from VC with chosen_hi
            If lo_v is not equal to 0:
                If hi_v is not equal to 0:
                    Let cmp3 be proc version_compare from VC with lo_v, hi_v
                    If cmp3 is greater than or equal to 0:
                        Set empty_check to 1
                    End If
                End If
            End If
            If lo_v is not equal to 0:
                proc version_destroy_deep from VC with lo_v
            End If
            If hi_v is not equal to 0:
                proc version_destroy_deep from VC with hi_v
            End If
        End If
    End If

    proc constraint_destroy_deep from VC with ca
    proc constraint_destroy_deep from VC with cb

    If empty_check is equal to 1:
        If chosen_lo is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with chosen_lo
        End If
        If chosen_hi is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with chosen_hi
        End If
        Return 0
    End If

    Let sb be proc stringbuilder_create from SB
    If sb is equal to 0:
        If chosen_lo is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with chosen_lo
        End If
        If chosen_hi is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with chosen_hi
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    If chosen_lo is not equal to 0:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, ">="
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, chosen_lo
    End If
    If chosen_hi is not equal to 0:
        If chosen_lo is not equal to 0:
            proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 32
        End If
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 60
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, chosen_hi
    End If
    Let out be proc stringbuilder_to_string from SB with sb
    proc stringbuilder_destroy from SB with sb
    If chosen_lo is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with chosen_lo
    End If
    If chosen_hi is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with chosen_hi
    End If
    Return out
End Process

@Reasoning
Compute the canonical lower-bound version string for a Constraint. For
EXACT(v), the lower bound is v. For RANGE >=lo <hi, the lower bound is
lo. For CARET(v), the lower bound is v. For TILDE(v), the lower bound
is v. For WILDCARD(major[.minor]), the lower bound is major[.minor].0.
For ANY, returns 0 (no lower bound).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Inspect constraint_kind. EXACT/CARET/TILDE/RANGE: extract the lower
Version field and stringify. WILDCARD: substring through the wildcard
position, append ".0" where missing.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns a fresh string (caller deallocates) or 0.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "lower_bound_string" takes c as Integer, original_spec as Integer returns Integer:
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let kind be proc constraint_kind from VC with c
    If kind is equal to 8:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let low be proc constraint_lower from VC with c
    If low is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc version_to_string from VC with low
End Process

@Reasoning
Compute the canonical upper-bound version string for a Constraint. For
EXACT(v), the upper bound is the next-greater version (synthesized by
incrementing patch). For RANGE >=lo <hi, the upper bound is hi. For
CARET(v) where v.major>=1, upper bound is (major+1).0.0; if major=0 and
minor>=1, upper bound is 0.(minor+1).0; if 0.0.*, upper bound is
0.0.(patch+1). For TILDE(v), upper bound is (major).(minor+1).0. For
ANY, no upper bound.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Branch on kind. Use constraint_upper for explicit ranges. For
caret/tilde, compute synthetically. Return as string.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns a fresh string (caller deallocates) or 0.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "upper_bound_string" takes c as Integer, original_spec as Integer returns Integer:
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let kind be proc constraint_kind from VC with c
    If kind is equal to 8:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let upper_v be proc constraint_upper from VC with c
    If upper_v is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc version_to_string from VC with upper_v
End Process

@Reasoning
Render a version-range spec as the canonical human-readable form. This
calls constraint_parse and serializes back to a normalized string.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Parse the spec, then produce a canonical form. For ranges, emit
">=lo <hi". For caret/tilde, preserve the original. For exact, emit
the version with no operator. For any, emit "*".
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input or parse failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "version_range_to_string" takes spec as Integer returns Integer:
    If spec is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let c be proc constraint_parse from VC with spec
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let kind be proc constraint_kind from VC with c
    If kind is equal to 8:
        proc constraint_destroy_deep from VC with c
        Return proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with "*"
    End If
    Let lo be proc lower_bound_string with c, spec
    Let hi be proc upper_bound_string with c, spec
    proc constraint_destroy_deep from VC with c
    Let sb be proc stringbuilder_create from SB
    If sb is equal to 0:
        If lo is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with lo
        End If
        If hi is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with hi
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    If lo is not equal to 0:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, ">="
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, lo
    End If
    If hi is not equal to 0:
        If lo is not equal to 0:
            proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 32
        End If
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 60
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, hi
    End If
    Let out be proc stringbuilder_to_string from SB with sb
    proc stringbuilder_destroy from SB with sb
    If lo is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with lo
    End If
    If hi is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with hi
    End If
    Return out
End Process
